com.mvohm.quadruple.test

Class TesterClasses.UnaryFunctionTester<S,R>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.mvohm.quadruple.test.TesterClasses.QuadTester
      • com.mvohm.quadruple.test.TesterClasses.UnaryFunctionTester<S,R>
  • Type Parameters:
    S - Source type for the tested operation
    R - Result type for the tested operation
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    TesterClasses.QuadOpTester
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    TesterClasses.Conversion_Q2T_Tester, TesterClasses.Conversion_T2Q_Tester, TesterClasses.UnaryQuadrupleFunctionTester
    Enclosing class:
    TesterClasses

    abstract static class TesterClasses.UnaryFunctionTester<S,R>
extends TesterClasses.QuadTester
    A common ancestor of the testers that test conversions, like Quadruple.toString() or Quadruple.assign(double), and unary operations.

    Defines abstract methods to be implemented by descendants:
    • performOp(Object) whose concrete implementations are to perform the tested operation,
    Implements protected methods (that can be overridden) to be used by descendants:
    • otherTypeName() -- to return the name of the type the conversion from which or to which is tested, or "Quadruple" for unary operations
    • makeExpectedItem(DataItem, String) -- to create a DataItem with the (provided or evaluated) expected value of the conversion,
    • findExpectedResult(Quadruple) -- to find the value that is expected to be the correct result of the conversion,
    • findExpectedString(Quadruple) -- to finds the string representing a value that can't be expressed as a BigDecimal

      • otherTypeName

        protected String otherTypeName()
        Returns the simple name of the source type for conversions from other types to Quadruple, or the simple name of the result type for conversions from Quadruple to other types, or "Quadruple" for unary operations. The default implementation returns "Quadruple".
        Returns:
        the simple name of the type participating in the tested conversion, other than Quadruple, or "Quadruple" for unary operations

      • makeExpectedItem

        protected DataItem makeExpectedItem(DataItem srcValue,
                                    String expextedString)
        Creates a DataItem with the expected value of the conversion. If the expected value is provided within the data sample, uses it, otherwise calculates the expected value using the findExpectedResult(com.mvohm.quadruple.Quadruple) and findExpectedString(Quadruple) methods that can be overridden by descendants.
        Parameters:
        srcValue - a DataItem containing the source value for the conversion being tested
        expextedString - the value of the string of the data sample that's intended to hold the expected value
        Returns:
        a DataItem containing the expected value of the conversion for the given source value

      • findExpectedResult

        protected BigDecimal findExpectedResult(Quadruple operand)
        The default implementation returns the BigDecimal value of the given Quadruple operand. If the value can't be represented as BigDecimal (NaN or Infinity), throws NumberFormatException. In cases of narrowing conversions, such as Quadruple.doubleValue(), descendants should override this method to provide the value that equals the corresponding value of the target type.
        Parameters:
        operand - the value to be converted
        Returns:
        the expected result of the tested operation as a BigDecimal

      • findExpectedString

        protected String findExpectedString(Quadruple operand)
        Returns a string representation of the calculated expected value. Specific testers, that has to return "NaN" or "Infinity" for some specific operands or operand combinations, ought to override this method. The default implementation returns null and does not use the parameter
        Parameters:
        operand - not used in the default implementation
        Returns:
        the default implementation returns null. Specific descendants that require this method should provide a proper value.
